    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="547"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d547">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/3320</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Irkutsk</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_HEL1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harris</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="2" xml:id="d547fn2">Sent via the Legation in China.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Omsk</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 29, 1918</hi>
                        </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received December 1, 11.04
                        a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>213. Vice Consul <persName>Thomas</persName> now stationed Chita reports as
                    follows: <pb facs="0540" n="450" xml:id="pg_450"/>
                    <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Concerning refusal <persName corresp="#p_SGG1">Semenov</persName> to
                            recognize <persName corresp="#p_KAAV1">Kolchak</persName>. <persName
                                corresp="#p_SGG1">Semenov</persName> staff says this applies not to
                            ministry but to <persName corresp="#p_KAAV1">Kolchak</persName>
                            personally. They expect <persName corresp="#p_KAAV1">Kolchak</persName>
                            resign but if not they say they are ready to declare autonomy of eastern
                            Siberia as temporary government, that they count on support of entire
                            eastern Siberia and possibly have agreement with <persName
                                corresp="#p_HGDL1">Horvat</persName>. Representative here of Omsk
                            government confident <persName corresp="#p_HGDL1">Horvat</persName> will
                            stand [by] <persName corresp="#p_KAAV1">Kolchak</persName> government
                            and that <persName corresp="#p_SGG1">Semenov</persName> will receive no
                            support outside his own small divisions and many people attribute
                                <persName corresp="#p_SGG1">Semenov</persName> action to Japanese
                            for two reasons: (1) <persName corresp="#p_KAAV1">Kolchak</persName> is
                            Anglophile and wishes Japanese troops withdrawn; [2] <persName
                                corresp="#p_SGG1">Semenov</persName> will prevent turning over the
                            Siberian Railroad to the United States on the principle that this could
                            not be done if United States will not recognize government here.</p>
                        <p>Representative people think the disorder is being caused for the benefit
                            of <persName corresp="#p_MAGD1">Michael</persName>, brother of
                                <persName>Tsar</persName>, who is rumored to be in Irkutsk. Such a
                            movement would receive wide support.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HEL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harris</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
